The article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring June 12-18, 2015, as the National Week of Making. The proclamation highlights the importance of American ingenuity and the role of makers, builders, and doers in pushing the country forward. The administration is committed to spurring manufacturing, innovation, and entrepreneurship by increasing access to resources and opportunities for Americans to build products and bring them to market. The proclamation also emphasizes the importance of engaging students in hands-on learning of STEM subjects and calls on all Americans to help unlock the potential of the nation. The week is meant to encourage programs and activities that promote making and manufacturing and empower the next generation of makers and manufacturers.